<page>
   <topic>UI_DLG_SHOW Function</topic>
     <description>Show a dialog.</description>
   <syntax>V UI_DLG_SHOW(C title)</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>title</name>
         <description>The name of the dialog box.</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
 
   <discussion>
The UI_DLG_SHOW()displays an invisible dialog box.
   </discussion>
  
   <sections>
       <section>
            <description>This example creates an invisible dialog with UI_DLG_CREATE(), then  displays it with UI_DLG_SHOW().
</description>
            <example><![CDATA[
ui_dlg_create("Invisible Xdialog", <<%dlg%
<20,3Click Here>
%dlg%)
ui_dlg_show("Invisible Xdialog")

]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
   <limitations>Desktop applications only.</limitations>
